<br>
Any healer spec'd in Aug can buff any tank (or skald) with a decent weapon to the attack speed cap.  A new buff for the same effect does nothing.<br>
And, given that the game recalibrated to calculating damage as damage per second, does speed really matter?  (Note that my standard hit doesn't interrupt a spell.  Narse the runemaster usually has to suffer a hit of over 150 damage for his spell to be interrupted.)  I'd argue no, speed doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
I have an alt, a healer with 50 aug (Ameria Seyruun).  Not completely useless, but given that her Purity of Aggression buff gives me the choice of decent hits, slowly, or little hits, quickly... who cares? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uaelodyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelodyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/14/02 1:44:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I'd argue no, speed doesn't matter.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Then why was it added to the Aug line? I can only assume that stacking the buffs will do something, otherwise, why waste time designing and implementing a new spell line? I'm going to give the Strike Team some credit and assume they know what they are doing.<br>
 <p><b>Ulf | Big Troll Skald | Kay</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dane>Dane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/14/02 1:56:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=187.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> Vivax, Aelodyn,<br>
<br>
From the Herald:<br>
Short duration group haste buff, stacks with concentration based haste <br>
18 Celerity <br>
<br>
It stacks.<br>
<br>
Point #2.<br>
<br>
The current healer haste gets you no where near the haste cap for most folks.  As we all know, haste = more effective on slower weapons.<br>
<br>
Quickness = 60 (no modifier I think at 60)<br>
Delay = 5.3s (2H great hammer)<br>
Hate = 20%<br>
Hasted delay = 4.24s<br>
<br>
That's nowhere near the 1.5s haste cap, and I don't know any healers that spec aug that high..most either have the 10% or 15% tops.<br>
<br>
IF you had 300 quickness AND a 20% haste buff, you would approach the cap.<br>
<br>
-Dane<br>
