<br>
I noticed that wardens who have shortbow got a pulling taunt, and berserkers with nothing got nothing, even after the change, and that they suddenly realised maybe an AE stun on a nuking class was a little overpowed (durr!)<br>
<br>
As for the bard changes...Well basically the situation with that is this - <br>
<br>
The three musical classes are meant to be very different. Dispite what someone said, bards are healer based not rouge, minstrels *are* rouge based and we are of course fighter based. However bards have basically been complaining that minstrels and skalds get insta-cast spells. Ignoring of course that both skalds and minstrels are from non-support class roots and non-caster roots and as such do actually need any spells to be instants. All our songs are sung rather then played too, because we are a fighter base and it'd make no sense to do it otherwise. However Bards don't have a lot of classes to compare themselves with as they are pretty unique, In actual fact the closest class to them is Shamans (being an addition healer based class that is neither of the clerical (lots of insta's) or the combo (good melee skill both offense and defence and 1.5spec) model), however bards *don't* compare themselves to shamans when they approach mythic, because that'd get them nerfed. Instead they compare themselves to less appropriate classes like ourselves in a bid to get what they want.<br>
<br>
So now they are in the enviable situation of being alowed to compare themselves to both skalds, and other healer based classes and get the best of both worlds.<br>
<br>
To be honest though I'm more pissed off for Shamans then Skalds. Mythic would never give Shamans a pb ae mez or anything that powerful, let alone 1.5 spec and weapon skill as well as already having 3 spell lines. Seems Shamans get the worst of all worlds while bards get the best.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong though, bards were a poorly designed class (like shamans) and had various issues. But mythic don't understand about fixing classes, if it requires too much work they'd rather throw in something quick, even if it then makes the class too powerful.<br>
<br>
Well anyway, I think if Bards can compare themselves to skalds we can compare ourselves to bards and demand rez or to get ae mez. <br>
<br>
I really don't have much faith in this strike team. They fobbed off shamans with crap (pb disease indeed) rather then giving them anything close to what they wanted, they messed up a lot of melee styles (like creating the new uber polearm one that was on fumble but is now on your opponent doing a style on you, which is easy to pull off in RvR, but it still has the bonuses as if it would hardly ever happen), they bend over backwards for bards and druids and give them exactly what the TL's asked for (they totally ignored the shamans suggestion, especially annoying as one of them was the same as the druids insta pb ae root, and yet it was considered reasonable for druids), they respond to angered earth wizards by making them even more uber then they made fire wizards (which was another dumb move, rather then fixing the class they just throw in uberness spells on top of the poor design), they put in two methods to let people use rarer styles, but the back up style made the cancel style redundant, and leaving the cancel style in just caused more problems in RvR, They sort out classes that can't pull, only they don't seem to know which classes can and can't pull (poor zerkers, they still haven't noticed them yet). They bungle the nerfing of clerics (again taking easy way outs rather then sorting things properly). I have to say when they announced the strike team I was hopeful, now I dread each change they make. <br>
<br>
Okay rant over. <br>
&lt;Deep Breath&gt;<br>
<br>
It really does bother me how much CC is being handed out to Albion/Hib, especially instant ones (or QCable). I already spend too long frozen to the spot in RvR. In Midgard we have only 3 classes that can mez, ours is on a timer and the spiritmasters is PB. We have only one class that can stun. It's apparently for realm balance that bards got the cure poison/disease and more importantly the AE mez. I think someone should point out to mythic our lack of stun and insta AE sleeps in midgard.<br>
